[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_mirds")
reagent_id = "Na2S"
title = "Sodium sulfide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]Na₂S[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]78 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]White to yellow solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
2Na + S → Na₂S  
Na₂O + H₂S → Na₂S + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of sodium and sulfur ions.  
• Soluble in water.  
• Reacts with acids to produce hydrogen sulfide gas (H₂S).
[b]Where sodium sulfide is found[/b]
• Produced in chemical industry from sodium compounds and sulfur.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Used in paper production.  
• Used in leather processing.  
• Used in some chemical manufacturing processes.
[b]Safety[/b]
Can release toxic hydrogen sulfide gas when reacting with acids.  
Can irritate skin and eyes."
